      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Airbnb is a global online marketplace that connects travelers with hosts offering short-term accommodations. With thousands of listings available in cities like New York, understanding pricing patterns, room type preferences, availability, and customer engagement is essential for both hosts and the platform.\n",
        "\n",
        "The problem is to analyze Airbnb listing data to identify patterns and relationships between different variables such as price, neighbourhood location, room type, availability, and reviews. By exploring these relationships through exploratory data analysis (EDA), we aim to gain insights that can help improve pricing strategies, identify popular locations, and understand factors that influence booking demand."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DpeJGUA3kjGy"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
