      "source": [
        "The exploratory data analysis of the Airbnb New York City dataset provides several insights that help address the business objective. By analyzing variables such as price, neighbourhood location, room type, availability, and number of reviews, meaningful patterns were identified that influence listing performance.\n",
        "\n",
        "The analysis shows that Manhattan and Brooklyn have the highest concentration of listings and higher pricing levels, indicating strong demand in these areas. Entire homes and apartments generally command higher prices compared to private or shared rooms, suggesting that property type plays an important role in pricing strategy.\n",
        "\n",
        "Additionally, the data indicates that moderately priced listings tend to receive more reviews, which may indicate higher booking frequency. This suggests that competitive pricing strategies can help hosts attract more customers and improve occupancy rates.\n",
        "\n",
        "From a business perspective, these insights can help Airbnb and hosts make better decisions regarding pricing strategies, listing availability, and location-based investments. By understanding these factors, hosts can optimize their listings to increase bookings, while Airbnb can enhance its recommendation systems and support hosts in improving their listing performance."
