        "## Conclusion\n",
        "\n",
        "In this project, an exploratory data analysis (EDA) was performed on the Airbnb New York City dataset to understand listing patterns, pricing trends, and host behavior. The analysis involved data cleaning, handling missing values, and visualizing relationships between different variables using various charts such as count plots, histograms, box plots, scatter plots, heatmaps, and pair plots.\n",
        "\n",
        "From the analysis, it was observed that **Manhattan and Brooklyn have the highest number of listings and the highest prices**, indicating that these areas are the most popular among travelers. Most Airbnb listings fall within the **affordable to mid-range price category**, with relatively few luxury listings. Entire homes and apartments tend to have higher prices compared to private or shared rooms.\n",
